{"word":"εὔδιος","slug":"εὔδιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὔδιος</b></el> <el>(εὔ-διος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δῖος'><el>δῖος</el></a>\n<p/><i>calm, fine, clear</i>, of weather, sea, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>:—<a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>εὔδιον, εὔδια</el>, as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:—<a href='S:irregular'>irreg.</a> <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>εὐδιαίτερος</el>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/>"}]}